From the previous exercise we have calculated the **Incremental cash flows** from the lessee's viewpoint as we show in figure 1:

<center><img src=" https://slader-solution-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/345f5d0b-82ca-4dfa-9171-48e237b238ae-1661393017266622.png " width="pixel">  <br>Figure 1. Incremental cash flows from the lessee.<p></p></center>

Now, by having the same tax rate $(21\%)$ we can have an analysis of the incremental flows for the lessor by considering a change of sign in the cash flows; what represents a positive flow for the lessee is a negative flow for the lessor and vice versa. 
Therefore, our incremental cash flow analysis is given in the following table:

$$
\begin{array}{c}
\textbf{Incremental Cash Flows for the Lessor}
\end{array}
$$

$$
